Fighter Guild Advancement
-------------------------

Fighters advance through battle. Every worthy kill earns Fighter XP, and
your guild level (1 to 15) rises automatically when you have earned enough.

Earning Fighter XP:
- Any NPC kill where you struck the killing blow, or dealt at least a
  tenth of the victim's health, awards Fighter XP to everyone in the
  group who qualifies.
- Tougher prey is worth more; prey ten or more levels beneath you is
  worth nothing. Bosses carry large bonuses.
- Variety pays. Hunting the same spawn over and over decays the reward;
  ranging widely keeps it at full value.

Guild levels:
- Levels advance on their own the moment you have earned enough XP.
- Your guild level can never exceed your character level, and your
  combined guild levels can never exceed your character level. XP earned
  while you are held back is banked, and the levels pop when you next
  advance your character.
- Guild level 15 is the pinnacle. XP earned beyond it is recorded, but
  buys nothing further.

Commands:
- 'fstats' shows your guild level and Fighter XP.
- 'cost' and 'advance guild' at the Grand Hall report your progress.
- Skills still unlock by guild level; see 'fs' for the list.

Your battle record survives leaving the guild. Should you return, your
standing is restored.
